cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with a deep learning architecture for image correction in MRI, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The proposed algorithm involves the use of iterative re-weighted least-squares implementation, which is related to information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for image processing is a common technique in neural engineering (cs.NE).
